00:14.440 --> 00:17.160
(PIANO PLAYING)

00:25.640 --> 00:28.235
(WOMAN VOCALIZING)

00:30.680 --> 00:31.750
(VOCALIZING STOPS)

00:38.960 --> 00:41.031
(CREAKS)

01:11.720 --> 01:13.871
(TWITTERING)

01:20.040 --> 01:21.394
(TWITTERING)

01:26.840 --> 01:28.957
(RUSTLING)

01:30.080 --> 01:31.434
(GROWLS)

01:42.760 --> 01:44.752
(TRAIN RATTLING)

01:59.480 --> 02:01.517
SUSAN:
It's not easy spending a day in the city

02:01.720 --> 02:04.076
with two kids around Christmastime,

02:05.440 --> 02:09.229
even if you have taken them
to a matinee and outdoor skating.

02:10.600 --> 02:13.600
I'd had to fight with them,
with Danny in particular,

02:13.760 --> 02:18.715
to get them aboard the 3:55 back
to the suburbs in time for dinner.

02:19.600 --> 02:22.115
Presents were still in his mind.

02:31.040 --> 02:32.360
What's in the box?

02:33.000 --> 02:34.036
SUSAN: Danny...

02:35.160 --> 02:36.230
leave the man alone.

02:37.760 --> 02:39.035
Present.

02:39.520 --> 02:41.512
- Can I see?
- SUSAN: Danny.

02:42.440 --> 02:43.999
Stop being so nosy.

02:45.040 --> 02:46.918
It's okay. No problem.

02:58.560 --> 03:00.711
Gotta go. My stop's next.

03:01.960 --> 03:04.111
P.A.: Brookfield next. Brookfield.

03:09.880 --> 03:11.917
JENNY: Come on, Danny. What'd he have?

03:12.960 --> 03:13.996
Who?

03:14.160 --> 03:15.833
The man, dummy, the one with the box.

03:16.240 --> 03:18.516
What was in the box?
The one on the subway.

03:18.680 --> 03:20.160
Oh. Nothin'.

03:20.320 --> 03:21.640
Nothing?

03:22.320 --> 03:23.879
You seriously mean it was empty?

03:24.040 --> 03:26.790
- There was nothing in there?
- ROBERT: Hey, guys. Chow's on.

03:27.320 --> 03:28.356
Great.

03:36.600 --> 03:38.592
What's the matter, squirt? Not hungry?

03:38.760 --> 03:39.989
DANNY: Not really.

03:40.880 --> 03:42.519
You, not hungry?

03:42.640 --> 03:43.710
You're always hungry.

03:45.680 --> 03:46.909
Did you get them something to eat

03:47.120 --> 03:48.349
when you were out?

03:48.640 --> 03:49.756
Just hot chocolate.

03:49.920 --> 03:51.798
With marshmallows and licorice.

03:52.000 --> 03:53.195
ROBERT: Nice.

03:54.280 --> 03:55.475
Can I go play?

03:59.480 --> 04:01.876
Sure. But I want those teeth brushed.

04:02.040 --> 04:03.713
- Yeah, Dad.
- ROBERT: All right.

04:07.880 --> 04:08.996
More?

04:15.160 --> 04:17.755
They're coming to get you, Barbara.

04:18.120 --> 04:19.634
- ROBERT: Want some, Danny?
- BARBARA: Stop it.

04:19.800 --> 04:21.075
- ROBERT: No? Wow.
- BARBARA: You're ignorant.

04:21.279 --> 04:22.396
MAN: (ON TV)
They're coming for you Barbara.

04:22.520 --> 04:23.431
More for us.

04:24.120 --> 04:26.237
BARBARA:
Stop it. You're acting like a child!

04:26.400 --> 04:27.629
MAN: (ON TV) They're coming for you.

04:27.800 --> 04:29.439
- Oh, my God. Look.
- Oh, look.

04:29.600 --> 04:31.080
MAN: (ON TV) Here comes one of them now.

04:31.240 --> 04:33.038
- (GROWLS) Raah!
- BARBARA: He'll hear you.

04:33.640 --> 04:34.960
SUSAN: Kids.

04:39.920 --> 04:40.990
No running.

04:41.600 --> 04:42.875
No, thanks, Mom.

04:43.880 --> 04:44.870
Daniel.

04:45.040 --> 04:46.076
Yeah, Mom?

04:47.160 --> 04:48.355
Don't forget your lunch.

04:49.040 --> 04:50.110
Thanks.

04:53.760 --> 04:55.672
(UTENSIL SCRAPING)

04:56.880 --> 04:59.554
(IMITATING WHOOSHES)

04:59.720 --> 05:00.710
ROBERT: What's going on?

05:00.880 --> 05:03.395
- You're not hungry again?
- Nope.

05:03.600 --> 05:05.000
It was pizza day at school.

05:05.840 --> 05:07.752
No, I skipped it.

05:08.600 --> 05:10.239
I find that hard to believe.

05:10.400 --> 05:11.834
Come on. Eat your ribs.

05:12.240 --> 05:13.879
No, thank you. I'm not hungry.

05:14.240 --> 05:16.516
(IMITATING WHOOSHES)

05:21.880 --> 05:24.670
ROBERT: He came home with his lunch
untouched again, you know.

05:25.320 --> 05:26.356
Really?

05:26.920 --> 05:30.798
He was probably sneaking junk food
in the cafeteria or something.

05:35.240 --> 05:37.436
I think we should make
an appointment with Dr. Weller.

05:38.080 --> 05:39.673
Maybe he's coming down with something.

05:42.680 --> 05:46.155
I'm sure it's just some stunt he's pulling
to get out of going to school.

05:46.360 --> 05:47.635
I wouldn't worry about it.

05:48.320 --> 05:49.754
Well, I am starting to get worried.

05:50.480 --> 05:51.880
Look, he doesn't have a fever.

05:52.960 --> 05:57.156
And even if he has the flu, there's nothing
Dr. Weller can do for him anyway.

06:00.600 --> 06:01.795
I guess so.

06:13.600 --> 06:15.398
ROBERT:
Listen, buddy, you gotta eat something.

06:17.800 --> 06:20.872
Danny, why didn't you eat
the lunch I made you today?

06:21.720 --> 06:23.120
I didn't feel like it.

06:26.480 --> 06:27.596
JENNY: Try some garlic bread.

06:27.920 --> 06:29.115
It's really good.

06:32.600 --> 06:33.829
You love spaghetti.

06:37.920 --> 06:39.149
No, thanks.

06:40.520 --> 06:42.193
It... It's been three days, buddy.

06:43.320 --> 06:44.640
Are you feeling okay?

06:45.920 --> 06:48.151
JENNY: Oh, my God.
It better not be the chickenpox.

06:48.320 --> 06:49.879
Amanda Dewsbury had the chickenpox,

06:50.040 --> 06:52.351
and she didn't show up for school
for, like, an entire week.

06:52.520 --> 06:54.916
She was covered in, like,
these disgusting, oozing sores...

06:55.080 --> 06:58.754
I feel fine, just not hungry.

07:00.960 --> 07:02.155
Okay.

07:09.480 --> 07:11.199
(FORK SCRAPING)

07:23.920 --> 07:26.151
Come on, Danny.
We made your favorite, pizza.

07:26.680 --> 07:27.830
Come on now.

07:29.080 --> 07:30.275
Not hungry.

07:35.080 --> 07:36.230
Smells good.

07:40.120 --> 07:42.919
(FORK SCRAPING)

07:47.200 --> 07:50.433
You're not getting up from this table until
you eat that pizza. Do you understand me?

07:51.280 --> 07:52.873
Do you understand me?

07:53.000 --> 07:55.469
Please, Danny, just take one bite.

07:57.480 --> 07:58.470
No, thank you.

07:58.640 --> 08:01.030
This has gone on long enough. Danny!

08:01.200 --> 08:03.271
God damn it, will you just eat?

08:03.440 --> 08:05.352
(CRYING) I'm not hungry.

08:12.520 --> 08:13.556
Fine.

08:14.080 --> 08:15.355
Then just go to bed.

08:17.120 --> 08:18.110
(ROBERT SIGHS)

08:23.680 --> 08:25.114
(ROBERT SIGHS)

08:34.760 --> 08:36.717
P.A.: Dr. Manson, circuit three.

08:46.400 --> 08:49.837
Any, uh, dizziness, vomiting, diarrhea?

08:50.000 --> 08:51.229
No, nothing.

08:51.640 --> 08:53.120
Fever, listlessness?

08:53.760 --> 08:55.479
No. He seems fine.

08:57.160 --> 08:58.958
And you say he hasn't eaten in five days?

08:59.120 --> 09:00.634
ROBERT: Absolutely nothing.

09:04.160 --> 09:05.753
Can I have a moment with him, please?

09:08.800 --> 09:09.756
Um, yeah, sure.

09:09.920 --> 09:11.593
- SUSAN: Sure.
- Thanks.

09:18.200 --> 09:19.350
Danny...

09:20.200 --> 09:21.111
Hmm?

09:21.280 --> 09:22.873
Is there anything you want to tell me?

09:27.040 --> 09:28.713
You sure? I mean...

09:29.760 --> 09:32.355
I'm here to listen. I wanna help.

09:34.160 --> 09:35.276
Everything's fine.

09:35.440 --> 09:37.079
I'm just not hungry, is all.

09:39.000 --> 09:40.195
You gotta eat, Danny.

09:42.680 --> 09:43.750
Why?

09:45.760 --> 09:46.989
Well, um...

09:47.960 --> 09:50.555
there's people starving
all over the world.

09:52.200 --> 09:53.680
I mean, if you don't eat...

09:54.320 --> 09:55.515
eventually you'll die.

09:56.240 --> 09:57.356
It's that simple.

09:59.400 --> 10:00.550
So?

10:02.360 --> 10:04.192
Why didn't you bring him in sooner?

10:07.600 --> 10:08.716
I don't know.

10:09.160 --> 10:11.436
Well, he's lost five pounds
since his last checkup.

10:12.160 --> 10:14.675
Other than that, he seems fine physically.

10:15.160 --> 10:16.435
We're gonna run some tests on him,

10:16.600 --> 10:18.990
and hopefully, uh,
it'll give us a clearer picture.

10:19.560 --> 10:21.392
Has he had any problems at school?

10:21.800 --> 10:22.870
- No.
- No.

10:23.320 --> 10:24.800
Nothing that we're aware of.

10:25.080 --> 10:25.991
DOCTOR: Home?

10:26.160 --> 10:28.231
No. Why do you ask?

10:28.920 --> 10:31.992
I think Danny might be having
some emotional problems.

10:36.280 --> 10:39.273
Now, there's a specialist
that I can recommend for you.

10:39.760 --> 10:40.955
A psychiatrist?

10:41.160 --> 10:42.913
No, a therapist, and don't worry.

10:43.120 --> 10:44.918
He's not gonna push any pills on Danny.

10:45.120 --> 10:46.270
He'll be there to help him.

10:46.440 --> 10:48.193
Well, how's he gonna help him, Doctor?

10:50.480 --> 10:52.437
Look, we're gonna
get to the bottom of this.

10:53.880 --> 10:56.270
Now, what I want you to do
is to call me every day

10:56.440 --> 10:58.837
and let me know how Danny's
doing, if he's eating.

10:59.000 --> 10:59.831
Okay.

11:00.000 --> 11:02.117
If he's not, don't push him.

11:02.280 --> 11:03.555
No, of course not.

11:03.760 --> 11:04.637
DOCTOR: All right?

11:04.800 --> 11:05.916
Stay calm.

11:06.080 --> 11:07.514
I'll keep you posted.

11:08.000 --> 11:09.912
- Thanks, Dr. Weller.
- Thanks.

11:28.840 --> 11:30.433
(SIGHS)

11:40.400 --> 11:42.039
(SOFT WHISPERING)

11:49.000 --> 11:50.354
JENNY: It doesn't make any sense.

11:51.320 --> 11:52.310
Hey.

11:53.120 --> 11:54.634
What are you guys talking about?

11:55.120 --> 11:56.190
- Nothing.
- Nothing.

11:56.960 --> 11:59.111
Come on. What were you just talking about?

11:59.920 --> 12:01.036
Just stuff.

12:02.560 --> 12:03.835
Secret stuff?

12:04.320 --> 12:05.754
Just, you know, stuff.

12:07.840 --> 12:10.355
Stuff that maybe has to do
with why you're not eating?

12:11.640 --> 12:12.994
That kind of stuff?

12:20.680 --> 12:21.511
Fine.

12:21.680 --> 12:23.273
Let's get back to bed.

12:32.640 --> 12:33.835
Jenny, what's the matter?

12:34.960 --> 12:35.996
Oh, nothing.

12:37.480 --> 12:38.516
Good night, Mom.

13:01.120 --> 13:02.031
SUSAN: Jenny.

13:02.200 --> 13:03.236
JENNY: Coming.

13:06.160 --> 13:07.037
Hey, Mom.

13:07.200 --> 13:08.111
Hey.

13:08.280 --> 13:09.430
Yeah, Mom?

13:10.360 --> 13:12.113
- It's chocolate.
- I'm okay.

13:12.280 --> 13:14.033
I'm not hungry. Thanks.

13:19.640 --> 13:20.790
(DOOR CLOSES)

13:29.880 --> 13:30.950
Where's Jenny?

13:32.520 --> 13:33.749
She says she's not hungry.

13:34.720 --> 13:35.790
Why?

13:37.320 --> 13:38.390
I don't know.

13:39.680 --> 13:40.909
I wish I did.

13:43.600 --> 13:45.432
Are you taking any of this seriously?

13:46.360 --> 13:47.589
Of course I am.

13:48.400 --> 13:49.675
I'm their mother.

13:50.400 --> 13:51.629
Well, I just don't understand it.

13:53.640 --> 13:54.710
Understand what?

13:55.880 --> 13:57.030
How you can eat

13:57.200 --> 13:58.839
while our children are starving.

14:02.440 --> 14:04.193
Well, I have to eat, don't I?

14:33.040 --> 14:34.952
(FOOTSTEPS)

14:37.680 --> 14:38.830
Danny.

14:46.200 --> 14:47.395
Hey.

14:52.080 --> 14:54.311
What is going on with you and Jenny?

14:57.840 --> 14:59.274
(SIGHS)

14:59.440 --> 15:01.432
Y... You know you can tell me.

15:07.440 --> 15:08.556
Please, tell me.

15:15.000 --> 15:17.435
(INDISTINCT WHISPER)

15:42.240 --> 15:43.515
What did he say?

15:43.680 --> 15:44.670
Huh?

15:45.480 --> 15:46.834
Danny.

15:47.400 --> 15:48.470
Oh.

15:49.560 --> 15:50.755
Nothing.

16:18.720 --> 16:21.360
(SCRAPING)

16:32.240 --> 16:33.754
Piece for you.

16:35.760 --> 16:37.194
Piece for you.

16:38.840 --> 16:39.910
There you go.

17:13.400 --> 17:16.199
(PIANO PLAYING)

17:25.720 --> 17:29.475
(INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE)

17:40.720 --> 17:45.233
SUSAN: I remember laughter
from that day, plenty of laughter.

17:47.320 --> 17:51.152
Nobody's new clothes fit,
but we tried them on anyway.

17:52.600 --> 17:54.831
Believe it or not, we were happy.

17:55.640 --> 17:58.553
We were more together
than we had ever been.

18:15.680 --> 18:16.830
Danny...

18:19.320 --> 18:21.471
do you remember that day on the train...

18:23.120 --> 18:24.520
the man with the box?

18:27.120 --> 18:28.952
Do you remember looking inside the box?

18:30.600 --> 18:31.716
Yeah.

18:33.880 --> 18:35.109
What was in it?

18:37.680 --> 18:38.955
Nothing.

18:42.160 --> 18:43.514
Really nothing?

18:44.920 --> 18:46.832
You mean it was actually empty?

18:50.800 --> 18:52.075
But I thought I...

18:54.920 --> 18:56.991
I remember him saying it was a present.

18:59.520 --> 19:01.193
Was he playing some kind of a joke?

19:03.840 --> 19:05.638
I mean, is this some kind of a joke?

19:11.680 --> 19:13.592
(MONITOR BEEPING)

19:21.880 --> 19:23.792
(VENTILATOR HISSING)

19:33.160 --> 19:35.072
(SECOND MONITOR BEEPING)

19:44.400 --> 19:46.312
(THIRD MONITOR BEEPING)

19:51.480 --> 19:54.393
(HEART BEATING, MONITORS BEEPING)

20:11.120 --> 20:13.715
(STEADY TONE SOUNDING)

20:13.880 --> 20:16.076
SUSAN: Danny died on January 17th.

20:17.880 --> 20:20.395
(TONE FADES)

20:20.560 --> 20:22.711
Jenny went on February third,

20:23.040 --> 20:26.033
and my husband Robert lingered
until the 27th.

20:29.840 --> 20:34.077
And through all of this,
through all these weeks now,

20:34.920 --> 20:37.992
going back and forth
to the hospital each day...

20:39.640 --> 20:41.154
I look for him.

21:17.920 --> 21:19.673
I need to find him...

21:22.560 --> 21:26.554
to know what my son knew and
then passed on to the others.

21:28.400 --> 21:31.199
It's the only way
I can get close to them now.

21:33.560 --> 21:35.153
I want to see.

21:36.320 --> 21:37.913
I have to see.

21:42.200 --> 21:43.395
I'm hungry.

21:46.400 --> 21:47.311
(PIANO PLAYING)

21:47.480 --> 21:49.392
(FOOTSTEPS)

21:55.360 --> 21:58.558
(CREAK)

21:58.720 --> 22:00.677
(INSECT BUZZING)

22:14.560 --> 22:16.472
(WHOOSH)

22:24.240 --> 22:26.152
(METAL TAPPING)

22:28.960 --> 22:30.872
(INSECT SKITTERING)

22:47.840 --> 22:49.752
(MUSIC PLAYING)

23:24.880 --> 23:25.916
Tsk.

23:37.600 --> 23:39.512
(TICKING)

24:01.320 --> 24:02.436
(GASPS)

24:03.640 --> 24:05.313
Good morning, Carla.

24:06.480 --> 24:07.516
Oh, thank you.

24:12.320 --> 24:15.074
The guests will be getting here
in less than an hour.

24:15.720 --> 24:18.280
I let Lucy sleep in.
She hasn't been sleeping well.

24:18.440 --> 24:19.556
You want me to wake her?

24:19.720 --> 24:23.157
Um, guess maybe wake her
in 15 if she's not up yet.

24:23.920 --> 24:24.990
Okay.

24:26.000 --> 24:27.434
Is that for David?

24:28.040 --> 24:29.440
- Yeah.
- Oh.

24:29.600 --> 24:32.872
No, I don't think Mr. Lampton will be
joining us at his daughter's birthday.

24:33.040 --> 24:35.032
His car was here
when I got in this morning.

24:35.720 --> 24:36.995
Must have gotten in late.

24:37.480 --> 24:38.630
No. No.

24:38.800 --> 24:40.917
He's not back from his trip yet.

24:41.120 --> 24:42.315
Maybe he's out for a run.

24:42.480 --> 24:43.755
I really doubt it.

24:44.920 --> 24:47.355
I think I would know
if he had come in last night.

24:47.520 --> 24:49.000
Yes, of course. I didn't...

24:49.160 --> 24:52.597
Okay. I... Well, I'll just take his, too.

24:53.080 --> 24:54.833
No use letting it go to waste.

24:55.960 --> 24:57.519
Can you, um...

24:58.080 --> 25:03.079
get the table runner from the hall closet,
and, uh, just put it on the side table.

25:03.240 --> 25:05.675
I think we're gonna do
gifts and cards over there.

25:06.240 --> 25:07.435
Yes, ma'am.

25:09.360 --> 25:10.350
Ooh, sorry.

25:13.920 --> 25:15.240
(SIGHS)

25:28.320 --> 25:29.356
(DOOR OPENS)

25:33.640 --> 25:34.960
(GASPS)

25:35.640 --> 25:36.960
David.

25:37.280 --> 25:41.354
God, between you and Carla,
you're gonna give me a heart attack.

25:41.560 --> 25:43.392
You know, I didn't even hear you come in.

25:43.600 --> 25:44.431
I don't know.

25:44.640 --> 25:46.233
Anyway, I'm just so glad that you're back.

25:46.400 --> 25:48.119
I really, really want this to go well.

25:48.280 --> 25:51.393
Lucy has been having such anxiety,
and I'm just really hoping that this

25:51.560 --> 25:52.994
brings her out of her shell.

25:53.360 --> 25:57.595
Do you know her therapist says that she
gets her anxiety from watching me?

25:57.760 --> 26:00.195
Me? (LAUGHS) Can you believe it?

26:00.360 --> 26:01.919
I mean, the nerve.

26:02.120 --> 26:04.237
It's just... Anyway, it doesn't matter.

26:04.400 --> 26:06.756
She's gonna be so glad that you made it.

26:11.440 --> 26:12.635
David?

26:16.840 --> 26:17.876
David...

26:23.920 --> 26:25.513
LUCY: Mom!

26:25.680 --> 26:27.114
Mommy!

26:27.280 --> 26:28.600
Where are you?

26:30.760 --> 26:31.876
Hi.

26:32.040 --> 26:33.554
I'm right here, panda.

26:33.720 --> 26:35.359
Good morning. Happy birthday.

26:35.520 --> 26:36.874
It's my birthday.

26:37.040 --> 26:39.874
I know. I know. It is your birthday.

26:40.840 --> 26:42.433
I had an accident.

26:42.960 --> 26:45.953
Oh, no. Oh, Luce, what happened?

26:51.400 --> 26:52.550
It's gonna be okay.

26:52.720 --> 26:53.995
All right?

26:54.160 --> 26:55.435
Everything's gonna be okay.

26:55.600 --> 26:56.795
You're gonna be okay.

26:57.320 --> 26:58.470
All right.

26:59.120 --> 27:00.713
Okay. We'll just...

27:01.160 --> 27:02.799
go find another costume.

27:09.560 --> 27:10.676
There we go.

27:10.840 --> 27:12.115
Scary ghost.

27:12.640 --> 27:14.438
LUCY: It's not scary at all.

27:14.600 --> 27:15.954
I look stupid.

27:16.120 --> 27:18.032
Sweetheart, you don't look stupid.

27:18.200 --> 27:19.475
You look great.

27:19.640 --> 27:21.472
I think it's gonna really be scary.

27:22.480 --> 27:24.199
- LUCY: Boo!
- (GASPS)

27:25.520 --> 27:27.557
There you go. (CHUCKLES)

27:27.720 --> 27:30.758
Got me, scary ghost. (CHUCKLES)

27:31.920 --> 27:32.956
Ohh.

27:34.000 --> 27:36.151
Why don't you go find Carla and show her?

27:36.640 --> 27:38.791
LUCY: Now I am a dead girl.

27:38.960 --> 27:44.558
Whoo! Whoo!

27:44.760 --> 27:45.671
(FADING) Whoo...

27:45.840 --> 27:48.309
(CRYING)

28:09.480 --> 28:10.596
(SNIFFS)

28:22.800 --> 28:24.473
Oh, David...

28:25.920 --> 28:27.274
you idiot.

