- (INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE)

35:49.320 --> 35:51.232
(CHILDREN LAUGHING, CHATTERING)

35:54.680 --> 35:56.831
(ROCK MUSIC PLAYING)

36:35.960 --> 36:38.191
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

36:42.320 --> 36:43.549
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

36:43.760 --> 36:45.672
(APPLAUSE, CHEERING)

36:58.120 --> 37:00.077
(ROCK MUSIC CONTINUES)

37:03.080 --> 37:05.675
(INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE)

37:22.360 --> 37:23.999
(ALL SCREAMING)

37:26.840 --> 37:28.752
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

37:48.520 --> 37:49.636
(SCREAMING STOPS)

37:54.040 --> 37:54.871
(PIANO PLAYING)

37:55.080 --> 37:56.150
(FEET TAPPING)

38:56.960 --> 38:58.474
(WIND BLOWING)

38:58.640 --> 39:00.552
(MUSIC PLAYING)

39:09.640 --> 39:12.872
GRETCHEN: Wait. How are we gonna know
if it is or if it isn't the right way?

39:13.040 --> 39:15.874
PAUL: I have an internal compass
that has failed me never.

39:17.520 --> 39:18.351
GRETCHEN: Wait.

39:18.520 --> 39:20.000
So the white scorpion
is the dangerous one?

39:20.160 --> 39:21.674
PAUL:
Just look out for translucent scorpions.

39:21.840 --> 39:23.957
GRETCHEN: I feel like all scorpions
are probably dangerous.

39:24.120 --> 39:26.670
PAUL: Yeah, I mean, they all hurt,
but the lighter the color the scorpion,

39:26.880 --> 39:27.791
the more dangerous it is.

39:27.960 --> 39:30.117
I wouldn't even worry about
the black ones. Just watch your step.

39:30.280 --> 39:32.556
GRETCHEN: Paul, I feel like
you do this to me all the time.

39:32.760 --> 39:34.717
Like when we were kids
and you told me that...

39:34.880 --> 39:38.792
the spider was gonna bite me
in the face and then lay eggs

39:39.320 --> 39:42.920
and then these baby spiders
were gonna hatch out of my skin

39:43.080 --> 39:44.230
in the middle of the night.

39:44.440 --> 39:46.796
- PAUL: 'Cause that shit happens.
- GRETCHEN: No, it doesn't.

39:46.960 --> 39:48.872
I didn't sleep for
a week. That's not even cute.

39:49.040 --> 39:51.437
PAUL: That happened to Jamie Preston's
brother in the fifth grade.

39:51.600 --> 39:52.795
- Hand to God.
- JAY: Jamie Preston?

39:52.960 --> 39:56.475
- That was the kid with the rash?
- GRETCHEN: No, that was his cousin.

39:56.640 --> 39:57.790
(CHATTER FADES)

40:10.320 --> 40:11.151
Whew!

40:11.320 --> 40:13.277
Whoo hoo hoo hoo hoo!

40:13.440 --> 40:14.556
Whoo!

40:15.840 --> 40:16.830
(EXHALES)

40:17.000 --> 40:18.150
Huh?

40:18.320 --> 40:21.279
GRETCHEN: Oh, my God. (GASPS)

40:21.480 --> 40:23.676
This is so fucking epic.

40:23.840 --> 40:24.956
PAUL: Right?

40:25.120 --> 40:28.516
This is why you guys should
let me do the planning every year.

40:28.680 --> 40:30.990
Paul, we'd end up
in a strip club in Vegas.

40:31.160 --> 40:32.958
JAY: Some booze cruise in Louisiana.

40:33.120 --> 40:35.237
PAUL:
Yes, how good was that, though? Seriously?

40:36.240 --> 40:39.153
GRETCHEN: Wow. We're really high up here.

40:39.320 --> 40:40.993
- JESS: Don't fall.
- (SCREAMS) Stop!

40:41.160 --> 40:43.117
- (LAUGHTER)
- That's not funny!

40:43.280 --> 40:44.760
JESS: Oh, babe, relax. I had you.

40:44.960 --> 40:46.076
JAY: Why would you do that?

40:46.240 --> 40:47.117
JESS: Because I had her,

40:47.240 --> 40:48.469
- so it was a great joke.
- JAY: Are you okay?

40:48.680 --> 40:50.353
Baby, are you seriously mad?

40:50.520 --> 40:51.636
Whoo!

40:52.400 --> 40:53.231
Right?

40:53.400 --> 40:54.914
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

40:55.080 --> 40:55.877
You want a picture?

40:56.040 --> 40:57.315
- Yep.
- Okay.

41:00.400 --> 41:01.550
Okay.

41:01.720 --> 41:02.676
What are you doing?

41:02.840 --> 41:04.035
- I'm just...
- Just be normal.

41:04.200 --> 41:05.077
Be normal.

41:05.240 --> 41:08.472
Ah, it's just really hot,
and you know I'm afraid of heights.

41:08.640 --> 41:09.869
Since when?

41:11.040 --> 41:12.474
What do you mean, "Since when"?

41:12.640 --> 41:13.835
Since forever.

41:14.000 --> 41:15.559
- I'm sorry.
- I'm, like, tired,

41:15.720 --> 41:17.837
and I'm communing with nature.

41:18.000 --> 41:20.151
- Okay. Okay.
- I have, like, one mo...

41:20.320 --> 41:21.879
What are you looking at?

41:23.280 --> 41:24.111
GRETCHEN: Oh, my God!

41:24.280 --> 41:25.509
- Is it a scorpion?
- JESS: No!

41:25.680 --> 41:26.830
GRETCHEN: I hate scorpions.

41:27.040 --> 41:28.759
- Is it white?
- (JESS LAUGHS)

41:28.960 --> 41:30.076
- Ow!
- I'm sorry.

41:30.240 --> 41:31.799
That time, I wasn't fucking with you.

41:31.960 --> 41:33.474
- JAY: You okay?
- She's fine.

41:33.640 --> 41:35.472
Seriously something creepy on this wall.

41:35.640 --> 41:36.756
- What happened?
- Yeah, I'm fine.

41:36.920 --> 41:38.036
Look.

41:40.480 --> 41:41.960
Oh, my gosh.

41:42.640 --> 41:43.994
Ah, cool.

41:44.160 --> 41:45.514
JESS: What does it mean?

41:46.000 --> 41:47.320
"Get off my lawn"?

41:47.520 --> 41:48.715
(LAUGHING)

41:48.880 --> 41:52.239
No, they paint them into the walls
to mark their territory.

41:52.440 --> 41:54.796
Ooh. Like ancient gang signs.

41:54.960 --> 41:56.189
Who's they?

41:56.600 --> 41:57.590
Indians?

41:57.760 --> 41:59.274
Paul, it's "Native American."

41:59.440 --> 42:01.272
That's the... what you're supposed to say.

42:01.440 --> 42:04.113
Older than that,
predates Native Americans for sure.

42:04.920 --> 42:06.115
That looks like blood.

42:06.280 --> 42:07.270
- Yikes.
- Gross.

42:07.440 --> 42:11.432
Well, all righty. Time to get moving
if we're gonna get back by dark.

42:11.880 --> 42:14.954
Wait. Wouldn't people native to America
before the Native Americans

42:15.120 --> 42:16.839
be called Native Americans?

42:17.000 --> 42:18.354
JAY: Not necessarily.

42:19.120 --> 42:22.400
Could be early homo sap
or homo novus,

42:22.600 --> 42:25.672
depending on what theory
of history you subscribe to.

42:43.720 --> 42:44.790
This is it, man.

42:44.960 --> 42:49.150
It's just us and the stars
and the best hiking around all weekend.

42:49.320 --> 42:50.436
Yeah.

42:51.560 --> 42:52.710
It's nice.

42:53.520 --> 42:56.996
That glamping place
that I booked in the... in the park,

42:57.160 --> 42:58.640
that was also really nice.

42:58.840 --> 43:00.035
That had showers.

43:00.200 --> 43:02.271
And it had screaming children.

43:02.440 --> 43:05.274
And paths where you can walk
and not get lost and...

43:05.440 --> 43:08.954
Trail markers made of crushed
Natural Ice cans from frat bros.

43:09.120 --> 43:10.918
Exactly. Thank you.

43:11.080 --> 43:15.114
This is the best campsite around, okay,
and nobody even knows about it.

43:15.320 --> 43:16.276
How'd you know about it?

43:16.440 --> 43:18.352
I just know shit, man, okay?

43:18.520 --> 43:21.356
I commune with nature,
and it shows me the way.

43:21.520 --> 43:23.637
- It shows him the way.
- (GRETCHEN LAUGHS)

43:23.800 --> 43:26.395
Or he bribed the gas station guy
at the last stop.

43:26.560 --> 43:27.391
PAUL: And also that.

43:27.560 --> 43:28.471
- GRETCHEN: What?
- That's true.

43:28.640 --> 43:30.154
- Are you kidding me? Paul!
- What?

43:30.320 --> 43:32.631
It could be, like, illegal for us
to be out here.

43:32.800 --> 43:34.439
This is like a historical
heritage site, clearly.

43:34.600 --> 43:37.473
- We could get arrested for that.
- Oh, come on.

43:37.640 --> 43:40.912
What? You think they want people
spray-painting dicks on those ancient murals?

43:41.080 --> 43:41.911
Hieroglyphs.

43:42.080 --> 43:42.911
Petroglyphs.

43:43.080 --> 43:44.275
Hieroglyphs are Egyptian.

43:44.440 --> 43:46.318
PAUL: Oh, my God.
I hate you so much sometimes.

43:46.480 --> 43:48.119
I don't think anyone's been
up here in a long time.

43:48.280 --> 43:49.953
Maybe it's cursed.

43:50.120 --> 43:51.440
It's not... You think it's cursed?

43:51.600 --> 43:53.990
(ROCKS CLATTER)

43:54.640 --> 43:55.676
What was that?

43:55.840 --> 43:56.910
PAUL: What was that?

43:57.880 --> 44:00.156
- No, Paul, don't do that.
- I'll check it out.

44:00.360 --> 44:01.919
No, no. Paul, please don't do that. Fuck.

44:02.080 --> 44:03.150
- Gretch, don't...
- Paul, please don't...

44:03.320 --> 44:05.198
Oh, my God! It's got me! Oh! Run!

44:05.360 --> 44:07.397
Gretch, don't entertain him.
You're just encouraging him.

44:07.560 --> 44:09.279
- I know. I fucking know he's...
- (PAUL SCREAMING)

44:09.440 --> 44:10.874
He's razzing me. I got it. I know.

44:11.080 --> 44:13.470
- (SCREAMING STOPS)
- (PAUL GASPS)

44:13.640 --> 44:14.551
Paul?

44:14.720 --> 44:16.040
JESS: Where the fuck did he go?

44:16.200 --> 44:18.510
I don't know. Paul, come on, dude.

44:18.680 --> 44:20.637
(CLATTER)

44:20.840 --> 44:22.718
I'm not... I'm not coming to get you.

44:22.880 --> 44:24.030
(CHUCKLES)

44:24.520 --> 44:25.476
He does this.

44:25.680 --> 44:27.592
You remember he did this
in the Adirondacks?

44:27.760 --> 44:31.037
He, like, wandered off, and then
he, like, broke his fucking ankle.

44:31.200 --> 44:33.112
- (SCREAMS)
- (LAUGHS)

44:33.280 --> 44:35.237
- I was just kidding.
- Don't, Paul.

44:35.440 --> 44:36.920
- That's not fucking funny.
- What?

44:37.080 --> 44:38.673
You love me. Come on.

44:38.840 --> 44:40.593
Okay, we're done fucking with her.

44:40.760 --> 44:42.513
Seriously. I'm going to bed.

44:42.680 --> 44:43.511
What? No!

44:43.680 --> 44:46.195
(GROANS) It's so early.
I was just fucking around.

44:46.360 --> 44:47.396
GRETCHEN: I'm not feeling good.

44:47.560 --> 44:48.516
How's your hand?

44:48.680 --> 44:50.797
- I don't know. It stings.
- Ohh.

44:50.960 --> 44:53.431
JAY: You can put some Neosporin on that.
It might get infected.

44:53.600 --> 44:54.920
Your face is infected.

44:56.080 --> 44:56.991
GRETCHEN: Infected?

44:57.160 --> 44:58.674
Okay. Where's the Neosporin?

44:58.880 --> 45:00.633
I have some in my bag.
You want me to show you?

45:00.840 --> 45:02.115
- No, I can get that.
- All right.

45:02.280 --> 45:03.475
Sleep well.

45:03.640 --> 45:04.869
JESS: Love you.

45:06.800 --> 45:07.870
Wow.

45:08.720 --> 45:09.915
Oh, man.

45:10.080 --> 45:11.992
I got way too stoned, you guys.

45:14.200 --> 45:16.192
(CHUCKLING)

45:16.400 --> 45:17.550
JESS: Oh, no.

45:19.360 --> 45:21.272
(COYOTES YIPPING)

45:47.160 --> 45:48.833
- (GASPS)
- (SOFT WHISPERING)

45:49.000 --> 45:51.071
(GROANING)

46:01.720 --> 46:02.790
(WINCES)

46:23.520 --> 46:24.874
What the fuck?

46:25.040 --> 46:26.872
(SNARLING)

46:27.040 --> 46:28.952
(SPEAKING GUTTURAL LANGUAGE)

46:30.240 --> 46:31.435
(GASPS)

46:32.480 --> 46:33.675
(SNARLS)

46:34.760 --> 46:36.672
(SHRIEKING)

46:41.120 --> 46:42.395
(SHRIEK ECHOES, FADES)

47:00.160 --> 47:01.913
- (SOFT SOB)
- Gretch?

47:02.400 --> 47:04.119
Gretchen, what are you doing?

47:04.280 --> 47:05.509
Hey, are you okay?

47:06.160 --> 47:08.152
Jay. We shouldn't be here.

47:08.320 --> 47:10.789
Hey. Gretchen, what is...

47:10.960 --> 47:12.235
- (PANTING)
- What's...

47:12.400 --> 47:13.880
JAY: What's wrong with you?

47:14.040 --> 47:15.679
- (BONES CRACKING)
- (GROAN ECHOES)

47:15.840 --> 47:17.035
(HISSES)

47:19.680 --> 47:20.557
(SNARLING)

47:20.720 --> 47:21.756
Gretchen?

47:21.920 --> 47:23.434
(DISTORTED) You shouldn't be here.

47:23.600 --> 47:24.670
(GROWLS)

47:27.160 --> 47:29.391
(GROWLING)

47:32.400 --> 47:35.438
(SHRIEK ECHOING)

47:38.040 --> 47:39.793
- (PANTING)
- PAUL: What the fuck, man?

47:40.000 --> 47:41.195
- Jay, what's happening?
- Jay.

47:41.360 --> 47:43.511
What are you... What time is it? What...

47:43.680 --> 47:45.080
Jay, what the fuck is happening?

47:45.240 --> 47:47.357
I don't know! I don't know! We have to go!

47:48.080 --> 47:48.877
Where's Gretchen?

47:49.040 --> 47:49.917
- Jay, what are you...
- Gretch?

47:50.080 --> 47:51.275
- What are you doing?
- Jay!

47:51.440 --> 47:53.477
What the fuck is going on? Say something!

47:53.680 --> 47:54.716
PAUL: Whoa! Stop, stop, stop!

47:54.880 --> 47:55.711
(PANTING)

47:55.880 --> 47:58.395
PAUL: Jay. Whoa, dude.
No, no, no, no! She's hurt!

47:58.600 --> 48:00.273
Wait! Wait! Wait! Get the fuck off me.

48:00.480 --> 48:02.199
- PAUL: That's my sister.
- JESS: Oh, my God.

48:02.360 --> 48:04.556
PAUL: Gretchen! Gretchen!

48:04.720 --> 48:06.871
JESS: This is so fucked.

48:08.360 --> 48:10.033
We have to leave now, okay?
You can't go out there.

48:10.240 --> 48:12.118
JESS: Why can't I go out there?
She's fucking hurt!

48:12.320 --> 48:13.151
JAY: Listen. Trust me.

48:13.320 --> 48:14.640
- What is your deal?
- Just trust me.

48:14.800 --> 48:15.790
I'm not leaving without Gretchen.

48:15.960 --> 48:19.397
- (PAUL SCREAMING)
- (CRUNCHING, TEARING)

48:19.560 --> 48:20.471
(SCREAMING STOPS)

48:20.640 --> 48:22.597
(GROWLING)

48:35.440 --> 48:37.238
(SLAM)

48:37.400 --> 48:40.279
(ROOF CREAKING)

48:40.440 --> 48:41.635
(THUMP)

48:43.840 --> 48:45.559
- (GASPING)
- Okay.

48:46.720 --> 48:47.790
Shh.

48:51.120 --> 48:53.032
(SOFT GROWL)

48:53.240 --> 48:55.311
(NAILS SCRAPE)

48:55.480 --> 48:57.278
(GASPING)

49:01.480 --> 49:03.392
(SHRIEKING)

49:04.480 --> 49:05.834
(SHRIEK)

49:07.280 --> 49:09.715
- JAY: Please. Ah...
- (MUTTERING)

49:09.920 --> 49:11.434
(HISSES)

49:11.600 --> 49:13.319
- Uh...
- (SNARLING)

49:13.480 --> 49:15.119
Open the door. Open the door.

49:16.760 --> 49:18.831
Okay. Okay.

49:22.000 --> 49:23.070
No. No.

49:26.400 --> 49:27.436
(GROWLS)

49:29.120 --> 49:30.679
- (GRUNTING)
- (CRACK)

49:30.840 --> 49:32.513
(HISSES)

49:34.480 --> 49:36.392
(GASPING)

49:42.120 --> 49:43.190
(WINCES)

49:44.640 --> 49:46.552
(GASPING, SOBBING)

50:12.960 --> 50:14.110
(SPLATTER)

50:27.480 --> 50:29.039
(GASPING)

50:29.200 --> 50:30.520
(SNARLS)

50:35.200 --> 50:36.873
Gretchen, it's me.

50:37.480 --> 50:38.880
(SOBBING) It's me.

50:39.040 --> 50:42.477
- (SNARLING)
- (BONES CRACKING)

50:42.680 --> 50:44.194
(HISSING)

50:44.360 --> 50:46.591
(SCREAMING)

50:48.160 --> 50:49.435
(SCREAM FADES)

50:49.600 --> 50:51.512
(MUSIC PLAYING)

50:53.120 --> 50:55.032
(SOFT WHISPERING)

51:10.640 --> 51:12.552
(THUNDER CRASHING)

51:22.360 --> 51:27.355
(HEART BEATING)

51:38.880 --> 51:41.714
(INSECTS BUZZING)

52:04.480 --> 52:05.516
(TICKING)

52:05.720 --> 52:07.074
WOMAN: So you believe me, Doctor?

52:08.720 --> 52:09.949
You actually believe me?

52:10.120 --> 52:12.635
I believe people have agendas.

52:14.680 --> 52:15.830
(SIGHS)

52:16.440 --> 52:18.159
DOCTOR: This crazy world, I swear.

52:18.760 --> 52:22.751
I'll go somewhere they'll never,
ever find me or little Andy or Jenny.

52:22.920 --> 52:24.070
Godspeed to you, Mrs....

52:24.280 --> 52:25.430
No.

52:26.160 --> 52:27.276
She's gone.

52:29.120 --> 52:29.917
(GASPS)

52:30.120 --> 52:31.600
(ALARM BUZZING)

52:31.760 --> 52:33.353
(DOG PANTING)

52:44.920 --> 52:46.832
(BUZZING CONTINUES)

52:48.000 --> 52:49.036
(BUZZING STOPS)

53:12.040 --> 53:14.032
(DOG BARKING)

53:14.200 --> 53:15.839
(WATER RUNNING)

53:16.040 --> 53:18.236
Come on. Come on.

53:19.520 --> 53:21.796
(BARKING)

53:21.960 --> 53:22.837
(WHIMPERS)

53:23.000 --> 53:24.354
ANDY: Dumb beast.

53:27.080 --> 53:28.514
(BARKING)

53:28.720 --> 53:30.234
- (BLOW LANDS)
- (DOG WHIMPERS, BARKS)

53:30.400 --> 53:32.357
- (BLOW LANDS)
- (WHIMPERS)

53:33.560 --> 53:35.472
(WHINING)

53:56.840 --> 53:59.230
You want anything special
for dinner tomorrow night?

54:01.200 --> 54:02.680
Maybe I'll roast a chicken.

54:06.000 --> 54:07.275
18.

54:08.760 --> 54:09.910
Doesn't make sense.

54:10.080 --> 54:11.230
Sure it does.

54:11.760 --> 54:13.399
I was born. Now I'm grown up.

54:13.600 --> 54:14.829
Almost grown up.

54:15.000 --> 54:18.035
Give me one more day to be
your mom before you get to vote.

54:18.400 --> 54:19.754
You're just sentimental.

54:26.360 --> 54:29.239
We could see that new movie
that Dad is in.

54:29.400 --> 54:32.517
Ohh. Of all the things you wanna do
for your birthday, that's it?

54:32.680 --> 54:33.909
Where has he ever been for you?

54:34.120 --> 54:37.595
How can he be there for me
when we're always hiding from him?

54:37.760 --> 54:39.717
Ambition can be an evil thing, honey.

54:39.920 --> 54:42.674
He'd rather be a Hollywood playboy

54:42.880 --> 54:45.600
than a real father to you,
and we're hiding for a reason.

54:45.800 --> 54:47.837
Not this again. I gotta go, Mom.

54:48.000 --> 54:50.754
He doesn't deserve
to have you in his life.

54:52.120 --> 54:53.918
I'm meeting with your teacher today.

54:54.080 --> 54:55.355
Do whatever you want.

54:55.920 --> 54:57.912
CORA: We need to talk
about what happened at school.

54:58.080 --> 55:00.231
ANDY: Go ahead. See what they say.

55:03.560 --> 55:05.631
(DOG BARKING)

55:05.800 --> 55:06.950
CORA: Kipper?

55:08.960 --> 55:10.872
(KIPPER WHIMPERING)

55:14.960 --> 55:16.110
What is it, boy?

55:16.280 --> 55:17.350
(KIPPER YIPS)

55:18.000 --> 55:19.070
(WHIMPERS)

55:21.200 --> 55:22.350
(SOFT BARK)

55:22.520 --> 55:24.079
(WHIMPERING)

55:37.160 --> 55:38.833
(BICYCLE BELL RINGS)

55:39.000 --> 55:40.150
Want your coupons?

55:40.320 --> 55:41.959
- Might as well.
- (CHUCKLES)

55:42.600 --> 55:44.557
Can't beat two-for-one tuna fish.

55:48.440 --> 55:50.113
- (SIGHS)
- (SIGHS)

55:50.480 --> 55:55.675
So, um, is Andy old enough to let you out
of the house for a night on the town?

55:56.200 --> 55:58.590
Well, that's... that's a nice suggestion,

55:58.760 --> 56:00.592
- but I don't think...
- I know.

56:00.760 --> 56:01.955
You're too busy.

56:02.600 --> 56:05.917
Ah, out of self-respect, I have to try
at least once a year. (CHUCKLES)

56:06.080 --> 56:08.549
I just thought you could
use a change of pace, is all.

56:09.520 --> 56:11.193
I appreciate that, Chet.

56:12.320 --> 56:14.073
It's kind of you to think of me.

56:14.240 --> 56:16.357
(SIGHS) Seems like you
haven't had it easy,

56:16.520 --> 56:18.830
and you've always done good by your kid.

56:23.040 --> 56:24.269
I'm late for my shift.

56:27.440 --> 56:28.317
(SCHOOL BELL RINGS)

56:28.480 --> 56:31.594
The incident was unfortunate,
but nothing that we feel requires...

56:31.760 --> 56:34.559
Unfortunate? Sir, are you on drugs?

56:34.880 --> 56:38.755
WOMAN: Now, there's no call for that
kind of hostile language, Mrs. Withers.

56:38.920 --> 56:40.320
(SIGHS) This is insane.

56:43.680 --> 56:49.559
Your son tore my daughter's
fingernails off, tore them clear off.

56:50.320 --> 56:54.438
She had to go to the emergency room,
her hands were bleeding so badly.

56:54.600 --> 56:57.314
I just don't understand
why he would do something like that.

56:57.480 --> 56:59.233
"Because I felt like it."

57:00.000 --> 57:01.639
That's what he told Stacy.

57:01.800 --> 57:05.589
He's just never been a violent or cruel...

57:05.760 --> 57:07.240
MRS. WITHERS: I hear the stories.

57:07.760 --> 57:10.480
I hear about the things
he makes the other kids do,

57:10.640 --> 57:13.109
all in the name of being
in the cool clique.

57:13.320 --> 57:16.438
Mrs. Withers, what about
Andy's side of the story?

57:16.600 --> 57:19.280
I mean, who's to say
he wasn't provoked at some point?

57:19.440 --> 57:21.716
Are you suggesting
that this is Stacy's fault?

57:21.880 --> 57:25.351
Conflicts like these
between hotheaded teenagers...

57:25.520 --> 57:27.955
Stacy is on her way

57:28.120 --> 57:30.510
to being valedictorian at this school.

57:30.680 --> 57:32.034
I would hardly call her...

57:32.200 --> 57:35.557
...are often very complicated situations.

57:35.760 --> 57:39.151
It's just not as black-and-white
as you're describing it.

57:39.840 --> 57:41.274
I am at a loss.

57:41.800 --> 57:45.075
He should be suspended
from school or expelled.

57:51.400 --> 57:53.392
What are you suggesting we do?

57:54.920 --> 57:57.719
I think it would be helpful if Stacy...

57:58.240 --> 57:59.640
takes a break from school,

57:59.800 --> 58:02.918
vacation, if you will,
until the dust settles.

58:03.320 --> 58:06.560
You can expect a call from our lawyer
later this afternoon.

58:08.800 --> 58:11.269
You've always been decent
to our family, Cora,

58:12.240 --> 58:14.197
but your son needs real help.

58:14.960 --> 58:19.433
And if you can't see that,
apparently so do you.

58:25.840 --> 58:26.990
(DOOR SLAMS)

58:27.160 --> 58:28.560
(SIGHS)

58:28.720 --> 58:31.918
I apologize that you
had to witness that outburst.

58:34.960 --> 58:35.996
You're...

58:36.880 --> 58:38.712
not going to punish him?

58:42.440 --> 58:47.517
You have to do something, or he's
never going to get the message.

58:48.120 --> 58:49.349
WOMAN: No, we don't.

58:50.120 --> 58:54.160
You see, Andy has sent a message to us.

58:55.200 --> 58:58.356
Over the course of these past
four years at this school,

58:59.440 --> 59:02.911
Andy has revealed himself to be
a truly remarkable human being.

59:03.080 --> 59:04.594
A prodigy, really.

59:05.200 --> 59:07.669
You see, every now and then,

59:07.840 --> 59:12.195
someone crosses our path
who will change the world as we know it.

59:13.560 --> 59:15.950
Andy is one of those people.

59:16.600 --> 59:21.758
I hope you will support all of our efforts
to protect what makes him so very special.

59:25.120 --> 59:27.351
We're so pleased that you could visit.

01:00:33.440 --> 01:00:34.840
(CUP RATTLING)

01:00:37.640 --> 01:00:39.040
WOMAN: You all right, hon?

01:00:39.560 --> 01:00:40.880
You don't look so good.

01:00:41.040 --> 01:00:42.838
I think my water broke.

01:00:44.920 --> 01:00:47.992
- (WAILING)
- WOMAN: Push, honey. Push!

01:00:48.200 --> 01:00:49.077
That's it.

01:00:49.240 --> 01:00:51.755
(WAILS)

01:00:55.440 --> 01:00:56.669
WOMAN: It's a boy.

01:00:58.840 --> 01:01:00.320
He's a little angel.

01:01:01.040 --> 01:01:02.076
No!

01:01:19.560 --> 01:01:20.676
(GRUNTING)

01:01:20.840 --> 01:01:22.752
(FLOOR CREAKING)

01:01:29.760 --> 01:01:32.229
(GROANING, GRUNTING)

01:01:32.400 --> 01:01:34.312
(THUMPING)

01:01:43.240 --> 01:01:44.276
Andy?

01:01:46.240 --> 01:01:47.913
(MUFFLED GRUNTING)

01:01:48.080 --> 01:01:49.196
Andy?

01:01:50.000 --> 01:01:51.354
Who's in there with you?

01:01:55.280 --> 01:01:57.112
My God, what happened?

01:01:58.520 --> 01:02:00.113
You know what I want for my birthday, Mom?

01:02:00.280 --> 01:02:04.479
Privacy. I want some fucking privacy!

01:02:05.160 --> 01:02:07.436
Andy, you told me
that you'd be out for the night.

01:02:07.600 --> 01:02:09.910
I was scared. I didn't know who...

01:02:10.320 --> 01:02:11.834
I didn't know who...

01:02:14.720 --> 01:02:16.120
(SLAMS DOOR)

01:02:34.760 --> 01:02:36.672
(SHUFFLING)

01:02:52.800 --> 01:02:54.154
Happy birthday, honey.

01:02:55.240 --> 01:02:56.833
Don't wait up for me tonight, Mom.

01:02:59.280 --> 01:03:01.192
(CLATTERING)

01:03:02.120 --> 01:03:03.190
(SLAMS DOORS)

01:03:04.280 --> 01:03:06.192
(SCRUBBING)

01:03:15.360 --> 01:03:17.272
(SCRUBBING)

01:03:33.040 --> 01:03:34.713
No rest for the weary. Am I right?

01:03:34.880 --> 01:03:37.315
(SIGHS) Chet. I am...

01:03:37.800 --> 01:03:38.756
a little weary.

01:03:38.960 --> 01:03:39.996
Hey, hey, hey.

01:03:40.160 --> 01:03:43.039
Why so glum, Cora?
Today's a beautiful day.

01:03:50.200 --> 01:03:55.116
Something's happening to Andy,
something just terrible.

01:03:55.280 --> 01:03:58.193
Ah, now, he's just growing up, is all,

01:03:58.360 --> 01:03:59.680
- becoming a man.
- No!

01:03:59.840 --> 01:04:02.560
He's not my Andy anymore.

01:04:02.920 --> 01:04:04.718
But he never really was, was he?

01:04:04.880 --> 01:04:06.473
What? What do you mean?

01:04:07.040 --> 01:04:10.556
I think it'll just get messy
the harder you fight him.

01:04:10.720 --> 01:04:12.552
But that's just it.
I don't wanna fight with him.

01:04:12.720 --> 01:04:14.040
- He's my son.
- No.

01:04:14.240 --> 01:04:15.720
Stop fighting him.

01:04:17.120 --> 01:04:19.914
Andy's real father
is coming to claim him soon.

01:04:20.120 --> 01:04:21.873
Andy's father has no interest in him.

01:04:22.080 --> 01:04:24.959
He lives on movie sets
with a girlfriend in every port.

01:04:25.120 --> 01:04:26.873
I can't imagine your ex really understood

01:04:27.040 --> 01:04:29.032
the agreement he made
back when he made it.

01:04:29.520 --> 01:04:31.398
(BIRD SQUAWKS)

01:04:31.560 --> 01:04:32.755
(FLY BUZZING)

01:04:32.920 --> 01:04:34.115
The agreement?

01:04:35.520 --> 01:04:36.920
He offered you.

01:04:38.760 --> 01:04:40.877
Who do you think he offered you to?

01:04:42.880 --> 01:04:45.554
Is it all coming back to you...

01:04:45.720 --> 01:04:46.756
"Cora"?

01:04:48.640 --> 01:04:49.756
Of course,

01:04:50.920 --> 01:04:52.036
I wasn't there.

01:04:52.480 --> 01:04:55.996
I only heard the story a thousand times,

01:04:56.200 --> 01:04:59.716
and I suppose the story
gets distorted over time,

01:04:59.880 --> 01:05:01.280
but it happened.

01:05:01.800 --> 01:05:04.110
And I have made my contribution.

01:05:04.680 --> 01:05:08.360
I'd like to believe that I've made
a difference in all this.

01:05:08.520 --> 01:05:12.431
I have been blessed
to watch over you all these years.

01:05:12.600 --> 01:05:14.114
No. No!

01:05:14.280 --> 01:05:15.396
And to watch over Andy,

01:05:15.560 --> 01:05:20.157
to prepare the world
for this glorious day!

01:05:21.120 --> 01:05:23.589
There's nothing to be afraid of, Cora!

01:05:24.280 --> 01:05:26.078
It's his time, is all!

01:05:29.200 --> 01:05:30.395
Praise...

01:05:31.520 --> 01:05:34.080
Praise His Darkness. Praise His Darkness.

01:06:44.920 --> 01:06:46.559
- (DOOR CLOSES)
- (GASPS)

01:06:52.000 --> 01:06:54.071
(FOOTSTEPS)

01:06:58.720 --> 01:07:01.030
(GRUNTS)

01:07:04.080 --> 01:07:05.514
(GASPS)

01:07:06.600 --> 01:07:08.114
(SNORTING)

01:07:18.720 --> 01:07:21.030
(SNORTING, GRUNTING)

01:07:22.880 --> 01:07:24.314
- (WINCES)
- (GASPS)

01:07:35.480 --> 01:07:39.235
(BANGING)

01:07:39.400 --> 01:07:40.516
(BESTIAL GROWL)

01:07:41.480 --> 01:07:42.516
(DOOR SLAMS)

01:07:54.480 --> 01:07:56.517
Andy, look at me.

01:07:56.680 --> 01:08:01.120
Some lady came up to me today,
calling me by my name.

01:08:02.120 --> 01:08:03.998
Never seen her before in my life.

01:08:04.160 --> 01:08:05.389
CORA: Andy, look at me.

01:08:06.440 --> 01:08:08.397
She said she knows my father...

01:08:09.880 --> 01:08:12.156
said he's been waiting
for me for a long time.

01:08:12.320 --> 01:08:15.633
Andy, I am your mother,
and I demand that you look at me.

01:08:15.800 --> 01:08:18.634
She said I was his only living son.

01:08:19.319 --> 01:08:20.754
Whose son, Mom?

01:08:20.920 --> 01:08:24.120
You told me Dad was remarried and living
in Hollywood with kids of his own.

01:08:24.279 --> 01:08:25.111
He is.

01:08:25.279 --> 01:08:26.999
He's had three wives since I left him.

01:08:27.200 --> 01:08:28.872
- What does she mean, Mom?
- I don't know.

01:08:29.080 --> 01:08:31.276
- She's crazy.
- What does she mean, Mom?

01:08:31.439 --> 01:08:33.193
What she said means nothing.

01:08:33.359 --> 01:08:35.716
You are my son. Do you hear me?

01:08:35.920 --> 01:08:39.514
We have not lived in town after town,
running from people like this for no reason.

01:08:39.680 --> 01:08:41.558
They're evil. They have an agenda.

01:08:41.760 --> 01:08:43.716
Don't listen to those words.

01:08:45.680 --> 01:08:46.670
You're special.

01:08:46.840 --> 01:08:48.069
You are. You always...

01:08:48.240 --> 01:08:50.037
(SHOUTS) I'm more than that, Mom!

01:08:53.640 --> 01:08:55.836
Sometimes, I just wanna hurt you...

01:08:57.240 --> 01:08:58.640
rip you to pieces.

01:08:58.800 --> 01:09:00.393
Don't say things like that.

01:09:00.560 --> 01:09:02.233
I have dreams

01:09:02.399 --> 01:09:05.711
of an empire of misery.

01:09:05.880 --> 01:09:08.600
Oh, honey, please stop
saying things like that.

01:09:14.760 --> 01:09:16.160
I want you to kneel.

01:09:20.680 --> 01:09:21.511
What?

01:09:21.680 --> 01:09:22.908
I said kneel.

01:09:24.840 --> 01:09:26.035
Kneel before me.

01:09:40.479 --> 01:09:41.470
That's it.

01:09:43.000 --> 01:09:44.229
Now crawl to me.

01:09:52.359 --> 01:09:54.272
(CRYING)

01:10:11.040 --> 01:10:12.554
(SNIFFLING)

01:10:19.800 --> 01:10:20.870
(GASPS)

01:10:25.960 --> 01:10:27.110
Oh, honey.

01:10:28.600 --> 01:10:30.273
I wanna go live with Dad now.

01:10:32.840 --> 01:10:34.069
You're my boy.

01:10:35.320 --> 01:10:37.437
You'll always be my boy.

01:10:37.600 --> 01:10:40.638
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:10:41.200 --> 01:10:42.680
I've got you, honey.

01:10:43.960 --> 01:10:45.280
- Don't look at him.
- (FLIES BUZZING)

01:10:45.440 --> 01:10:46.874
Just close your eyes.

01:10:47.040 --> 01:10:48.440
Listen to the story.

01:10:49.760 --> 01:10:51.513
At first, you made me so unwell.

01:10:51.720 --> 01:10:54.076
God, I had never felt so awful
as those first three months.

01:10:54.240 --> 01:10:58.238
I ate raw liver and saltines, and other
than that, I couldn't keep a thing down.

01:10:58.440 --> 01:11:01.874
You just took the life out of me,
and you took and took

01:11:02.040 --> 01:11:03.872
until one day, I said, "I've had enough."

01:11:04.040 --> 01:11:06.236
And I swear, honey,

01:11:06.840 --> 01:11:09.196
deep in my belly, you heard me cry.

01:11:09.680 --> 01:11:11.956
You heard how much pain I was in,

01:11:12.160 --> 01:11:15.358
because you and I are bonded,

01:11:16.120 --> 01:11:17.759
no matter who your father is.

01:11:17.960 --> 01:11:19.792
(SIGHS) The perversion.

01:11:20.000 --> 01:11:21.957
It's something unholy they did to me.

01:11:22.120 --> 01:11:24.714
And when I found out those sick people
wanted you for their own,

01:11:24.920 --> 01:11:27.440
I went to the doctor
I should have seen in the first place,

01:11:27.600 --> 01:11:31.396
and I told him our crazy story,
and Andy, Andy, he believed me.

01:11:31.560 --> 01:11:33.438
And he gave us enough money
to leave the city,

01:11:33.640 --> 01:11:35.711
